Package gw.plugin.lookup

Interface LookupMetadata

public interface LookupMetadata
LookupMetadata is an interface for defining Lookup metadata on a Lookup Table.

LookupMetadata is used for constructing lookup request definition.

    • getTableID

      Unique Id for identifying lookup table.
      Returns:
      TableId for lookup

    • getTableName

      String getTableName()
      Table name or Lookup function name. This name should be unique, no conflict with other lookup table/function names within the same Plugin implementation.
      Returns:
      Lookup Table Name

    • getInputs

      List<LookupMetaColumn> getInputs()
      Return list of Lookup input parameters that should require to execute lookup function. (These input parameters will be used for constructing Lookup request definition and execute the Lookup at runtime).
      Returns:
      Lookup table input parameters
